339
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:40,012
Doctor.

340
00:19:40,879 --> 00:19:42,948
Please be honest with me.

341
00:19:44,716 --> 00:19:46,485
If I get hospitalized now,

342
00:19:47,719 --> 00:19:49,254
as you say,

343
00:19:49,755 --> 00:19:52,057
when will I be able to

344
00:19:53,425 --> 00:19:54,426
go back to work?

345
00:19:55,060 --> 00:19:57,729
-That is…
-In one month?

346
00:19:58,664 --> 00:20:00,199
In three months?

347
00:20:00,799 --> 00:20:02,134
I can't say for sure.

348
00:20:03,402 --> 00:20:04,670
Well then…

349
00:20:06,972 --> 00:20:11,577
I'd better do what I need to do
before that, right?

350
00:20:11,643 --> 00:20:12,778
But…

351
00:20:14,246 --> 00:20:17,349
Do you have any family members
who can come?

352
00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:18,984
Anybody who can support you--

353
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:21,220
I told you I don't have anyone!

354
00:20:23,455 --> 00:20:25,023
So tell me…

355
00:20:26,525 --> 00:20:28,894
If I'm not hospitalized now,

356
00:20:28,961 --> 00:20:30,095
how long

357
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:32,664
will I have to live?

358
00:20:35,167 --> 00:20:36,935
How long will I live?

359
00:20:37,502 --> 00:20:40,706
Unless you start treatment right away,
you might only have

360
00:20:40,772 --> 00:20:42,307
three months to live.

361
00:20:56,455 --> 00:20:57,789
That's enough.

362
00:21:04,763 --> 00:21:06,965
What the heck?

363
00:21:07,032 --> 00:21:09,434
What's the point in uncovering

364
00:21:09,501 --> 00:21:11,837
the deeds of someone who is dead?

365
00:21:12,671 --> 00:21:17,175
Is this the kind of journalism
I wanted to do?

366
00:21:34,593 --> 00:21:35,861
Reiko?

367
00:21:35,927 --> 00:21:37,996
Sensei, this is bad. Really bad.

368
00:21:38,864 --> 00:21:40,132
Calm down, will you?

369
00:21:40,198 --> 00:21:43,335
<i>Josei Eight</i> published an article
about you and Masaki.

370
00:21:47,472 --> 00:21:49,174
THE EIGHTH AND TRUE ILLEGITIMATE CHILD!

371
00:21:49,241 --> 00:21:50,876
THE SHAMELESS PROFESSOR EMERITUS YABUUCHI

372
00:21:53,211 --> 00:21:54,346
<i>You know,</i>

373
00:21:54,413 --> 00:21:58,350
<i>once I set my eyes on a target,</i>
<i>I never miss.</i>

374
00:21:58,417 --> 00:22:00,752
<i>…it sells for an even higher price</i>
<i>the second time around.</i>

375
00:22:02,721 --> 00:22:04,823
Excuse me, I'm from <i>Weekly Genjitsu</i>.

376
00:22:04,890 --> 00:22:07,392
I have a few questions about your mother.

377
00:22:08,026 --> 00:22:09,961
-Mom…
-Will you please come out?

378
00:22:27,846 --> 00:22:31,817
‪SODEN PUBLISHING‬

379
00:22:37,622 --> 00:22:38,590
What was that for?

380
00:22:44,930 --> 00:22:46,631
Is bullying the weak

381
00:22:47,499 --> 00:22:49,334
what you call "journalism"?

382
00:22:51,236 --> 00:22:53,872
In what way is that article
in the public interest?

383
00:22:55,173 --> 00:22:56,441
Shame on you.

384
00:23:00,512 --> 00:23:02,614
I don't want to hear it from a hyena.

385
00:23:09,621 --> 00:23:11,590
You damn vulture!

386
00:23:11,656 --> 00:23:13,058
-What?
-A fight?

387
00:23:14,126 --> 00:23:16,161
It's a fight.

388
00:23:17,829 --> 00:23:20,499
-What are you doing? Stop that!
-Damn you!

389
00:23:20,565 --> 00:23:22,134
Hey! Stop!

390
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:25,237
POLICE STATION

391
00:23:25,303 --> 00:23:27,372
SECURITY PATROL

392
00:23:29,274 --> 00:23:30,108
Sensei!

393
00:23:32,411 --> 00:23:34,246
If Ms. Reiko hadn't called me,

394
00:23:34,312 --> 00:23:36,281
you would've been in trouble.

395
00:23:36,348 --> 00:23:38,250
Hageta was taken to the hospital,

396
00:23:38,316 --> 00:23:40,118
but he only had minor injuries.

397
00:23:40,185 --> 00:23:42,320
Sensei, are you okay?

398
00:23:42,387 --> 00:23:44,523
Yeah, somewhat.

399
00:23:45,524 --> 00:23:47,893
Harming the media is viewed as a threat

400
00:23:47,959 --> 00:23:49,561
to freedom of expression--

401
00:23:49,628 --> 00:23:51,463
Who was the one who truly

402
00:23:52,731 --> 00:23:53,799
did harm?

403
00:23:58,403 --> 00:23:59,905
Reiko, lend me your bike.

404
00:23:59,971 --> 00:24:02,340
Hey. I'm still talking to you.

405
00:24:17,923 --> 00:24:20,058
Do you feel a little better now?

406
00:24:31,403 --> 00:24:33,405
My father who raised me

407
00:24:34,606 --> 00:24:36,374
was a bus driver.

408
00:24:38,376 --> 00:24:41,012
He started a small bus company

409
00:24:42,414 --> 00:24:43,682
and was working hard.

410
00:24:46,451 --> 00:24:47,919
Up until 18 years ago,

411
00:24:48,687 --> 00:24:51,556
when he died during a driving accident,

412
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:55,994
I thought that he was my real father.

413
00:24:58,230 --> 00:24:59,364
That's how much

414
00:25:01,199 --> 00:25:02,767
of a good father he was.

415
00:25:05,470 --> 00:25:08,306
It was an unfortunate accident
caused by strong winds.

416
00:25:09,608 --> 00:25:10,709
But

417
00:25:11,376 --> 00:25:12,878
before we knew it…

418
00:25:15,247 --> 00:25:17,415
the media started to spread stories about

419
00:25:17,482 --> 00:25:19,484
how my father fell asleep at the wheel.

420
00:25:20,886 --> 00:25:22,320
At his court case…

421
00:25:24,489 --> 00:25:26,658
they even manipulated his verdict.

422
00:25:28,260 --> 00:25:29,394
That's terrible.

423
00:25:30,996 --> 00:25:34,065
The one who pressured
the judge into doing that…

424
00:25:36,001 --> 00:25:38,637
was a big shot in the legal world,

425
00:25:38,703 --> 00:25:40,105
Kengo Jidori.

426
00:25:42,908 --> 00:25:43,942
<i>My…</i>

427
00:25:44,676 --> 00:25:47,379
biological father.

428
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:50,582
What?

429
00:25:53,151 --> 00:25:54,252
I…

430
00:25:55,353 --> 00:25:58,056
became a lawyer in order to clear

431
00:25:58,123 --> 00:25:59,624
my father's name.

432
00:26:00,692 --> 00:26:01,860
However,

433
00:26:02,694 --> 00:26:04,796
the moment I got a hold of evidence that

434
00:26:04,863 --> 00:26:06,298
proved Jidori's involvement,

435
00:26:07,132 --> 00:26:08,400
they silenced me…

436
00:26:10,936 --> 00:26:13,405
by spouting a bunch of lies about me.

437
00:26:14,105 --> 00:26:16,441
That's why you were
shunned by the legal community?

438
00:26:16,975 --> 00:26:17,909
Yeah.

439
00:26:21,446 --> 00:26:23,815
Is your debt…?

440
00:26:24,549 --> 00:26:28,587
<i>Maybe we should've renounced inheritance</i>
<i>like the lawyer said?</i>

441
00:26:31,756 --> 00:26:33,058
I…

442
00:26:34,793 --> 00:26:36,061
don't want to run away.

443
00:26:39,431 --> 00:26:40,832
I don't want to back down.

444
00:26:44,035 --> 00:26:45,103
Because

445
00:26:45,704 --> 00:26:47,472
I believe your father.

446
00:26:49,174 --> 00:26:52,310
Part of it was paid
by the insurance company.

447
00:26:53,178 --> 00:26:56,715
But still, the remaining compensation
was an enormous amount.

448
00:26:58,416 --> 00:27:00,218
Jidori wanted my mother and I to

449
00:27:01,419 --> 00:27:03,989
be burdened by that
for the rest of our lives.

450
00:27:10,328 --> 00:27:11,563
Mom…

451
00:27:13,131 --> 00:27:15,166
would've been able to live

452
00:27:16,501 --> 00:27:18,737
a happier life if I wasn't born.

453
00:27:21,573 --> 00:27:23,775
I don't think that's true.

454
00:27:27,078 --> 00:27:29,147
Look at my mother…

455
00:27:30,882 --> 00:27:32,617
In the end, mothers

456
00:27:34,486 --> 00:27:36,454
love their children.

457
00:27:37,889 --> 00:27:38,957
Plus,

458
00:27:40,859 --> 00:27:42,494
if you were to ask me,

459
00:27:44,896 --> 00:27:47,165
I would not be

460
00:27:49,401 --> 00:27:51,136
alive now if I hadn't met you.

461
00:27:56,875 --> 00:27:59,511
This might sound weird but…

462
00:28:05,183 --> 00:28:07,686
thank you for being born.

463
00:28:33,878 --> 00:28:35,714
Good morning.

464
00:28:42,954 --> 00:28:45,590
Hello, this is
Haie Inheritance Investigation Office.

465
00:28:45,657 --> 00:28:47,358
<i>Attorney Fukushi?</i>

466
00:28:47,425 --> 00:28:48,860
Is Haie there?

467
00:28:49,794 --> 00:28:52,297
Sensei…

468
00:28:53,431 --> 00:28:56,301
