541
00:33:50,428 --> 00:33:52,397
-Everything tastes amazing!
-Stop.

542
00:33:53,131 --> 00:33:54,966
You suck at describing food, Sensei.

543
00:33:56,634 --> 00:33:59,003
I've never had meat that was this tender.

544
00:34:01,539 --> 00:34:04,142
It's called Shinshu Wagyu.

545
00:34:05,576 --> 00:34:06,711
Go ahead

546
00:34:07,311 --> 00:34:08,413
and have this one too.

547
00:34:08,980 --> 00:34:10,081
Really?

548
00:34:10,815 --> 00:34:12,350
-Here.
-Thank you.

549
00:34:12,417 --> 00:34:13,484
Enjoy.

550
00:34:23,494 --> 00:34:24,629
What's wrong?

551
00:34:27,864 --> 00:34:30,802
I wish I could let my mother eat this too.

552
00:34:37,341 --> 00:34:39,476
Oh, I'm sorry. That was weird.

553
00:34:48,052 --> 00:34:49,987
Come back for a meal anytime.

554
00:34:50,054 --> 00:34:51,121
Okay?

555
00:34:51,188 --> 00:34:52,590
I'll make anything.

556
00:34:56,327 --> 00:34:57,528
It'll be

557
00:34:58,429 --> 00:35:00,298
lonely all by myself, anyway.

558
00:35:03,267 --> 00:35:04,769
Thank you.

559
00:35:10,942 --> 00:35:13,444
I'm glad it worked out.

560
00:35:14,846 --> 00:35:16,714
Even if it's a complicated relationship,

561
00:35:16,781 --> 00:35:18,916
sometimes people just get along.

562
00:35:19,484 --> 00:35:22,086
On the other hand,
some can never get along.

563
00:35:22,153 --> 00:35:24,856
Are you talking about you and me?

564
00:35:24,922 --> 00:35:26,557
-Oh!
-Ugh!

565
00:35:26,624 --> 00:35:29,260
To what do I owe this honor,

566
00:35:29,327 --> 00:35:31,496
Great Attorney Fukushi?

567
00:35:32,763 --> 00:35:35,066
I made time out of my busy schedule.

568
00:35:38,169 --> 00:35:39,770
Vulture, for some reason,

569
00:35:39,837 --> 00:35:43,040
is not going to press charges
for your assault.

570
00:35:43,608 --> 00:35:44,742
Vulture said that?

571
00:35:45,676 --> 00:35:47,545
Does he finally feel a little sorry?

572
00:35:47,612 --> 00:35:48,579
You idiot.

573
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:53,217
Vulture apparently asked
the editor in chief

574
00:35:53,284 --> 00:35:55,453
to not publish his article.

575
00:35:55,520 --> 00:35:57,088
However,

576
00:35:57,155 --> 00:35:59,524
the article made it out.

577
00:35:59,590 --> 00:36:01,425
-Huh?
-Really?

578
00:36:02,226 --> 00:36:03,461
Yes.

579
00:36:03,528 --> 00:36:06,030
-Then why…
-…did the article get published?

580
00:36:07,932 --> 00:36:10,635
<i>I'll make sure to teach him</i>
<i>what will happen</i>

581
00:36:11,202 --> 00:36:13,604
if he does anything unnecessary.

582
00:36:17,041 --> 00:36:18,309
Maybe

583
00:36:18,910 --> 00:36:21,812
they were pressured to do so by somebody.

584
00:36:29,754 --> 00:36:30,821
Haie,

585
00:36:31,522 --> 00:36:34,325
I've been recruiting
Ms. Reiko for a while.

586
00:36:34,392 --> 00:36:35,726
Even if she stays with you,

587
00:36:35,793 --> 00:36:38,196
there is nothing she can gain.

588
00:36:39,463 --> 00:36:42,133
I want her to come to my office.

589
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:43,034
How about it?

590
00:36:44,235 --> 00:36:47,438
Attorney Fukushi,
I will have to turn down your offer--

591
00:36:47,505 --> 00:36:48,673
No.

592
00:36:50,341 --> 00:36:51,742
Reiko

593
00:36:51,809 --> 00:36:54,345
is a super capable assistant.

594
00:36:54,412 --> 00:36:56,414
Please offer her
the best working conditions.

595
00:36:57,715 --> 00:37:00,017
-Sensei, what are you…?
-Of course.

596
00:37:00,084 --> 00:37:03,421
I plan to give Ms. Reiko
whatever she asks for.

597
00:37:03,487 --> 00:37:05,256
Well then, that's settled.

598
00:37:05,323 --> 00:37:07,658
Why? Why are you making decisions for me?

599
00:37:07,725 --> 00:37:09,493
Now, calm down.

600
00:37:10,494 --> 00:37:12,230
Great Attorney Fukushi,

601
00:37:12,296 --> 00:37:14,232
will you leave us alone for a bit?

602
00:37:27,845 --> 00:37:29,814
Sensei, I'm not going, all right?

603
00:37:32,450 --> 00:37:34,085
Reiko…

604
00:37:36,020 --> 00:37:37,188
The thing is…

605
00:37:38,956 --> 00:37:41,959
I decided to close this office.

606
00:37:47,431 --> 00:37:48,332
Huh?

607
00:37:51,302 --> 00:37:52,903
Why is that?

608
00:37:54,038 --> 00:37:57,308
There's something I want to
really focus on.

609
00:37:58,542 --> 00:38:00,077
So I want you

610
00:38:00,711 --> 00:38:02,446
to go to Fukushi's place.

611
00:38:02,513 --> 00:38:04,515
Wait a second!

612
00:38:04,582 --> 00:38:06,550
The thing you want to focus on…

613
00:38:08,085 --> 00:38:09,787
I can be of help to you.

614
00:38:09,854 --> 00:38:10,855
No…

615
00:38:11,689 --> 00:38:12,690
It's okay.

616
00:38:14,025 --> 00:38:15,593
Plus,

617
00:38:16,160 --> 00:38:17,995
I'm sure you'll be able to

618
00:38:20,131 --> 00:38:22,166
do more at Fukushi's office.

619
00:38:24,001 --> 00:38:26,570
You'll be able to save money
to go back to medical school.

620
00:38:26,637 --> 00:38:28,639
You have your mother to worry about too.

621
00:38:47,124 --> 00:38:48,559
Fine.

622
00:38:49,160 --> 00:38:50,995
I don't agree with you, but I'll comply.

623
00:38:55,866 --> 00:38:57,735
-Reiko.
-Yes?

624
00:39:00,471 --> 00:39:01,572
Thank you,

625
00:39:03,341 --> 00:39:04,709
you’re un-bee-lievable.

626
00:39:06,644 --> 00:39:07,778
How cheesy.

627
00:39:28,499 --> 00:39:30,668
HAIE INHERITANCE INVESTIGATION OFFICE

628
00:39:45,216 --> 00:39:48,052
Ms. Reiko really quit, huh?

629
00:39:50,221 --> 00:39:51,522
It's better that way.

630
00:39:53,758 --> 00:39:54,859
I guess.

631
00:39:57,361 --> 00:39:58,396
Well then,

632
00:39:59,029 --> 00:39:59,930
what shall we do?

633
00:40:01,232 --> 00:40:03,367
First, we'll reveal who used their power

634
00:40:03,434 --> 00:40:05,770
to force the publishing
of Vulture's article.

635
00:40:05,836 --> 00:40:07,071
Then…

636
00:40:08,372 --> 00:40:10,508
I'll settle the score for my Dad.

637
00:40:12,643 --> 00:40:16,680
But how will we find new evidence?

638
00:40:25,523 --> 00:40:26,390
Ms. Reiko.

639
00:40:26,891 --> 00:40:28,459
SEBUMI LAW OFFICE

640
00:40:28,526 --> 00:40:29,794
Welcome.

641
00:40:29,860 --> 00:40:30,795
Sup.

642
00:40:32,062 --> 00:40:33,230
Everyone,

643
00:40:33,297 --> 00:40:35,533
this is our new secretary,

644
00:40:35,599 --> 00:40:37,535
Ms. Reiko Mitomi.

645
00:40:37,601 --> 00:40:38,803
Applause.

646
00:40:38,869 --> 00:40:39,804
She looks cool.

647
00:40:39,870 --> 00:40:42,506
-Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

648
00:40:54,051 --> 00:40:56,420
The difference is like heaven and hell.

649
00:40:57,154 --> 00:40:59,256
Or a luxury hotel and a stable.

650
00:41:01,292 --> 00:41:04,195
My goodness, without Ms. Reiko around,

651
00:41:04,261 --> 00:41:06,464
this place is worse than a stable.

652
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:13,370
Hello, this is
Haie Inheritance Investigation Office.

653
00:41:13,437 --> 00:41:15,439
I'm sorry, but we're closing this office--

654
00:41:15,506 --> 00:41:16,507
<i>Hey.</i>

655
00:41:17,007 --> 00:41:18,542
Hyena.

656
00:41:19,543 --> 00:41:21,345
Oh, it's just a vulture.

657
00:41:22,213 --> 00:41:24,882
<i>I haven't forgotten</i>
<i>how you punched me the other day.</i>

658
00:41:24,949 --> 00:41:25,783
That…

659
00:41:26,584 --> 00:41:27,985
You don't have to apologize.

660
00:41:28,752 --> 00:41:30,821
But in exchange, I want to talk.

661
00:41:31,555 --> 00:41:34,291
<i>I see that some judge named Jidori</i>

662
00:41:34,358 --> 00:41:36,026
<i>really hates you.</i>

663
00:41:37,027 --> 00:41:39,663
I know what happened
to your dad's bus accident.

664
00:41:39,730 --> 00:41:41,065
You…

665
00:41:41,131 --> 00:41:43,534
<i>Listen carefully.</i>

666
00:41:43,601 --> 00:41:45,636
I have information that will

667
00:41:45,703 --> 00:41:47,404
overthrow Jidori.

668
00:41:47,471 --> 00:41:50,674
It's a huge scoop.

669
00:41:50,741 --> 00:41:51,976
First of all,

670
00:41:52,476 --> 00:41:54,645
the one who pressured the magazine

671
00:41:54,712 --> 00:41:57,081
<i>to publish my article that I tried to stop</i>

672
00:41:57,581 --> 00:41:58,849
<i>was Jidori.</i>

673
00:42:00,818 --> 00:42:02,086
I knew it.

674
00:42:02,152 --> 00:42:05,823
He might have done that
because he really hates you.

675
00:42:06,690 --> 00:42:09,093
His skills at gathering information
are impressive.

676
00:42:09,159 --> 00:42:11,495
But why now?

677
00:42:11,562 --> 00:42:14,231
Hyena, what do you think

678
00:42:15,299 --> 00:42:16,967
about joining forces with me?

679
00:42:18,102 --> 00:42:20,004
<i>Even if I make a fuss on my own,</i>

680
00:42:20,070 --> 00:42:21,405
the enemy is too powerful

681
00:42:21,472 --> 00:42:23,140
and I'll be silenced right away.

682
00:42:25,976 --> 00:42:27,945
You want to avenge

683
00:42:28,479 --> 00:42:29,747
your dad, don't you?

684
00:42:33,918 --> 00:42:37,721
Humans can die at any moment.

685
00:42:37,788 --> 00:42:40,357
If that's the case, I thought

686
00:42:40,424 --> 00:42:42,026
it was time to show the public

687
00:42:42,092 --> 00:42:44,528
my passion for journalism,

688
00:42:44,595 --> 00:42:46,430
so that I can die at any time

689
00:42:46,497 --> 00:42:47,631
without regrets.

690
00:42:48,365 --> 00:42:51,035
I want to go up against

691
00:42:51,101 --> 00:42:53,270
real evil this time.

692
00:42:53,871 --> 00:42:55,139
What people would call

693
00:42:55,205 --> 00:42:57,942
"the corruption of the judicial system."

694
00:42:59,176 --> 00:43:02,179
A useless second-rate reporter
like you, huh?

695
00:43:03,113 --> 00:43:06,250
<i>You're one to talk,</i>
<i>pathetic second-rate detective.</i>

696
00:43:08,552 --> 00:43:10,921
If two second-rates get together,

697
00:43:12,056 --> 00:43:13,657
our force still doubles.

698
00:43:24,902 --> 00:43:27,905
I have 50 million yen in savings.

699
00:43:28,639 --> 00:43:30,374
I have no family.

700
00:43:31,041 --> 00:43:32,810
I'll hire you

701
00:43:32,876 --> 00:43:34,411
for 50 million yen.

702
00:43:34,979 --> 00:43:36,747
I want you to

703
00:43:37,781 --> 00:43:39,717
back me up until the end.

704
00:43:44,288 --> 00:43:46,056
I'm willing to listen.

705
00:43:46,123 --> 00:43:47,558
Come to my office.

706
00:43:49,193 --> 00:43:50,294
Idiot.

707
00:43:50,928 --> 00:43:52,429
I'm already here.

708
00:44:20,057 --> 00:44:21,325
Answer me!

709
00:44:21,392 --> 00:44:23,360
And the mutual enemy is Jidori.

710
00:44:23,427 --> 00:44:24,995
Please save Sensei.

711
00:44:25,062 --> 00:44:25,996
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita
